# Agent authority PREFLIGHT

**REQUIRED.** When this turn will use any **skill**, **MCP**, or **project rule**, the agent’s **first visible reply** in that turn MUST open with a PREFLIGHT block. Do not hide it in thoughts only.

## When it fires

Emit PREFLIGHT if any of these are true for the turn:

- Loading or following a skill (`.cursor/skills/**`, `.agents/skills/**`, agent skill menus)
- Calling MCP (`GetMcpTools`, `CallMcpTool`, `FetchMcpResource`, or any MCP server tool)
- Applying project rules (`.cursor/rules/**`) or `AGENTS.md` authority beyond trivial chitchat
- Product routing via `/using-afenda-elite-skills`

Skip only for pure chitchat with **no** skill load, **no** MCP, and **no** rule-driven work.

## Exact block (copy shape)

```text
### PREFLIGHT
- Engaging: skills | mcp | rules (list which apply)
- Skills: <name(s) or none>
- MCP: <server/tool(s) or none>
- Rules: <rule file stem(s) or none>
- Router: using-afenda-elite-skills | n/a
```

Then continue the turn (tools allowed after this block).

## Always-apply baseline (Rules line)

When the turn applies project rules (including `alwaysApply`) or edits product/package code, name the **rule file stems** that apply under **Rules**. Baseline stems commonly include:

| Stem | When |
|------|------|
| `agent-authority-preflight` | Any PREFLIGHT-firing turn |
| `coding-discipline` | Product/package code edits or typed hygiene this turn |
| `no-shim-stub-tech-debt` · `no-mvp-quality-bar` · `no-park-defer-false-yagni` | Product work (and whenever those bans apply) |

**Skills vs Rules:** list `afenda-coding-discipline` under **Skills** only when that skill was loaded this turn. The always-apply floor is **`coding-discipline`** (Rules) — do not invent the skill name under Skills to “cover” the rule.

## Forbidden

- Starting tool calls that load skills / call MCP / depend on rules **without** the PREFLIGHT block first
- Vague “I’ll use some skills” without naming them
- Claiming a skill/MCP/rule was used without PREFLIGHT on that turn
- Listing `afenda-coding-discipline` under Skills when only the `coding-discipline` rule applied

## Hook enforcement

`.cursor/hooks/agent-authority-preflight.mjs` reminds on `sessionStart`, skill/rule reads (`postToolUse`), and MCP (`beforeMCPExecution`). Reminder ≠ substitute — the agent must still self-declare in the user-visible reply.

Authority: [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) · companion hooks in `.cursor/hooks.json`.
